The paper focuses on the performance of hybrid precoding structures for massive multiuser MIMO systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT), multimedia (cs.MM), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer communication networks (cs.COM). The use of limited feedback channels and quantized analog and digital precoding also suggests a focus on information theory and communication systems.
